entry.content:
This reverts commit f26b7ae855b4530c3b358312eec788a1368dbcf8.



Reason for revert: PasswordGenerationIntegrationTest is failing on multiple builders



Bug: 1439122, 1421753, 1433296



Original change's description:

> Reland "[TTFPassGen] Move PasswordGenerationAgent::FocusedElementChanged call earlier"

>

> This is a reland of commit 3c1a89031d0a3c5ef1c89a89c637ca80b1bcc629

>

> The original CL was reverted because of the failing PasswordManagerUIUtilAndroid::ShouldNotAcceptFocusEventAfterLoosingFocus test (it's renamed to ShouldNotAcceptFocusEventAfterFrameLostFocus currently) on the android-bf-cache bot. The test was re-writted and now passes.

>

> > [TTFPassGen] Move PasswordGenerationAgent::FocusedElementChanged call earlier

> >

> > Now PasswordGenerationAgent::FocusedNodeHasChanged is called from AutofillAgent::DidCompleteFocusChangeInFrame, which happens later then the virtual keyboard is shown (when a text input element is navigated).

> > It feels more natural to move the FocusedNodeHasChanged call to AutofillAgent::HandleFocusChangeComplete, which happens before triggering the keyboard. This is needed for the password generation bottom sheet (the bottom sheet should be able to suppress the keyboard before it's triggered).

entry.title: [Code Health] Migrate BackgroundFetchRegistration to GC mojo wrappers.
entry.content:
BackgroundFetchRegistration's registration_service_ becomes a

HeapMojoRemote, and thus is initialized with an execution context.



This means that when the registration service is bound with the

registration interface, it needs a task runner. Since this task runner

is moved in this process, it needs to be a different task runner than

the one already used in the ctor.



Because the execution context provides the task runner, in the case of

a nullptr or destroyed execution context, the registration service

will not be bound; this is a change from the prior implementation.



Fixed: 1426369

entry.content:

domainSuffixMatch or subjectAltNameMatch.

values of domainSuffixMatch and subjectAltNameMatch are not controlled

by the user in this case.

entry.title: Mojo API for opening URLs without interception by URL capturing.
entry.content:
The gotcha is that the JavaScript `window.open(url)` has a page

transition of `ui::PAGE_TRANSITION_LINK`, which can be intercepted by

URL capturing.

- Specifying a different page transition prevents interception logic.

- I chose `ui::PAGE_TRANSITION_FROM_API` [1] which suits our use case,

i.e. transition originating from an external application.



Note that this function only accepts https:// URLs and will always open

the specified URL in a new browser tab.

- Failure to provide a valid https:// URL will cause the Help app

renderer process to crash.



[1]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:ui/base/page_transition_types.h;l=137;drc=3e1a26c44c024d97dc9a4c09bbc6a2365398ca2c

construct `NGInlineBreakToken`.

entry.title: autocorrect: add another logic to stop showing Undo window if the 'suggested text' does not match the text within the 'autocorrect range' [Lacros Mitigation]
entry.content:
In Lacros, for example,

AC autocorrects "ChromeOS |" into "Chrome OS |".



Step 1. Move the cursor in between "Chrome OS", e.g. "Chrome |OS", the press backspace, "ChromeOS".



The undo window is still present and shown, which is a bug.



Step 2. Click "Undo", chromeos crashes.



Currently, this is a bug on Lacros that keeps showing the undo window even when users delete some characters of the suggested words. Clicking Undo in this case will cause a crash.



This CL temporarily patches that issue by forcing the undo window to close if some letters are detected to be different from the suggested words.

entry.title: Fix crash when casting from quick settings with multiple monitors
entry.content:
When there are multiple monitors attached, casting from quick settings

causes a desktop picker window to open. This causes a window activation

and closes quick settings. With the QsRevamp flag enabled, this causes

a call to CloseBubble() after the CastDetailedView has been deleted,

which is a use-after-free and causes a crash.



Fix by not attempting to close the bubble if the view is deleted

(because the bubble was already closed).
